§ 65_GPU_MEMORY_TYPE_DISTINCTION · CPU↔GPU-memory-as-distinct-types ¬ storage-class-annotation
  ← author : Tech-Lead-agent · 2026-05-14
  ← supersedes : —
  ← superseded-by : —
  ← status : DRAFT
  ← scope : cross-cutting (types · effects · capabilities · MIR · codegen)
  ← parent-template : specs/_TEMPLATE.csl
  ← discipline : authored under specs/64_SPEC_FIRST_DISCIPLINE.csl
  ← consumer : LoA v13 PRISM (PRISM_v13.md §2.4 CPU/GPU split · §4.3 Role-C host engineer)

§I THESIS
  ⟦
    CSSLv3 today distinguishes CPU vs GPU execution via the @gpu / @c / @cross
    attribute set + storage-class annotations on buffers. This catches "wrong-target
    function call" but does NOT catch the deeper class of bugs : accidentally
    dereferencing a GPU pointer from CPU code · double-mapping a buffer that's
    still being written by another queue · reading staged data before its transfer
    completed · forgetting that ReBAR-mapped memory has weak ordering across the
    PCIe boundary.
    
    This spec elevates memory-domain to a FIRST-CLASS TYPE DISTINCTION. A `gpu<T>`
    and a `T` are NOT interconvertible by reinterpretation · they are different
    types. Cross-domain access requires an explicit transfer-op whose typed signature
    proves : (a) the destination domain accepts this type · (b) any queues that
    were writing the source have synchronized · (c) the IFC labels propagate
    correctly across the PCIe boundary. The compiler refuses code that elides
    these steps.
    
    The directly-consumed payoff : PRISM_v13's ReBAR + async-compute architecture
    becomes a typed feature rather than a careful-coding-convention. The structural
    payoff : an entire class of Vulkan/D3D12 lifetime bugs becomes unrepresentable.
  ⟧

§I OBSERVABLE-ASSERTIONS [MANDATORY]
  ⟦
    ASSERT.01 · csslc compile of `fn bad() { let x : gpu<f32> = ... ; let y = *x }` from a
                @c context fails with diagnostic GPU0001 "cross-domain deref of gpu<T> in CPU
                code · use download() or shared<T>"
    ASSERT.02 · csslc compile of `let s : shared<f32> = alloc_shared(...); write_gpu(s, ...); read_cpu(s)`
                without an intervening `barrier()` fails with diagnostic GPU0003 "shared<T> read
                without preceding write→read barrier"
    ASSERT.03 · csslc compile of `upload(x : f32) -> gpu<f32>` produces a MIR op
                `cssl.gpu.transfer.h2d` that lowers to a vkCmdCopyBuffer on Vulkan,
                CopyBufferRegion on D3D12, or memcpy-into-rebar-window when target supports it
    ASSERT.04 · Sensitive<gaze> values cannot be cross-domain-transferred without
                Cap<TransferAuth> + matching IFC declass-policy · compile-error GPU0007
                "Sensitive label egress across PCIe boundary without declass"
    ASSERT.05 · golden-test : the existing v13 PRISM intersection shader compiles
                AS-IS when memory-type annotations are added to its inputs · bit-equal output
                against the un-annotated reference for 100 representative rays
    ASSERT.06 · spec-65 implementation reduces a benchmark "intentional CPU-on-GPU-ptr deref"
                test-program from "runtime segfault" to "compile error" · automated test in
                csslc/tests/spec-65-cross-domain-deref.cssl
    ASSERT.07 · async-compute test : two-queue write+read on a `shared<T>` without a
                cross-queue semaphore compiles to GPU0008 "cross-queue access without
                explicit semaphore on shared<T>"
    ASSERT.08 · ReBAR-fallback test : on host without ReBAR-capable hardware, `alloc_shared`
                emits a build-time warning + falls back to staged<T> pattern · runtime exits
                successfully with the v13 PRISM 320×200 render unchanged · pixdiff zero
  ⟧

§I MEMORY-DOMAIN-TYPES (the type-system additions)
  ⟦
    base-types (existing) :
      T          · CPU-resident value of type T · the default · backwards-compatible
    
    new-domain-tags :
      gpu<T>     · GPU-resident · cannot-CPU-deref · cannot-CPU-write
                   constructor : upload(t : T) -> transfer<gpu<T>>
                   destructor  : download(g : gpu<T>) -> transfer<T>
                   read-from-@gpu-fn : transparent ¬ ceremony
      
      shared<T>  · ReBAR-mapped · BOTH CPU + GPU can access
                   has memory-ordering tag : { Coherent · WeakOrdered · NonCoherent }
                   default = WeakOrdered (ReBAR canonical · explicit barrier required)
                   constructor : alloc_shared(layout : ShareLayout, n : usize)
                                  -> Result<shared<T>, AllocError> · requires Cap<Shared>
                   access      : read_cpu(s) · write_cpu(s, val) · read_gpu(s) · write_gpu(s, val)
                   barriers    : barrier_c2g(s) · barrier_g2c(s) · barrier_full(s)
      
      staged<T>  · CPU-side staging buffer · queued for upload · not-yet-on-GPU
                   constructor : stage(t : T) -> staged<T>
                   commit      : commit_upload(s : staged<T>) -> transfer<gpu<T>>
                   eliminated-if-shared-available : compiler chooses shared<T> when ReBAR present
      
      transfer<T> · proof-token of an in-flight transfer · NOT a value
                   inhabitants : await(t) -> T · cancel(t) -> ()
                   linear-resource per §§ 12 CAPABILITIES · must be consumed exactly once
                   cross-queue : transfer is queue-tagged · awaiting from different queue
                                  requires explicit semaphore-wait
    
    cross-domain-arrow : the only legal cross-domain transitions
      T          → upload    → transfer<gpu<T>>     · await → gpu<T>
      gpu<T>     → download  → transfer<T>          · await → T
      T          → stage     → staged<T>            · commit → transfer<gpu<T>>
      T          → alloc_shared → shared<T>          · with Cap<Shared>
      shared<T>  → read_cpu  → T                    · with barrier_g2c precedent
      shared<T>  → read_gpu  → gpu<T>               · with barrier_c2g precedent  (from @gpu)
      shared<T>  → drop_shared → ()                 · with Cap<Shared> · linear
    
    forbidden (compile-error GPU0001-GPU0010) :
      *gpu<T>    in @c context                       · GPU0001
      *cpu_T     in @gpu context-without-upload      · GPU0002
      read_cpu(shared<T>) without barrier_g2c        · GPU0003
      transfer<T> dropped-without-await              · GPU0004 · linear-leak
      transfer<T> awaited-on-different-queue-without-semaphore · GPU0005
      gpu<Sensitive<*>> direct-transfer-to-cpu       · GPU0006
      Sensitive<gaze|face|body|biometric> across PCIe · GPU0007 absolute · ¬ Cap-overridable
      cross-queue access shared<T> without semaphore · GPU0008
      shared<T> via alloc_shared without Cap<Shared> · GPU0009
      shared<T> on non-ReBAR-host without fallback   · GPU0010 (warning-not-error · degrades to staged)
  ⟧

§I MEMORY-ORDERING-TAGS (the ReBAR / async-compute substrate)
  ⟦
    shared<T> carries a memory-ordering parameter at the type-level :
      shared<T, Coherent>    · OS-coherent · CPU and GPU see same value at-all-times
                                rare · expensive · use only for control-channel mailboxes
      shared<T, WeakOrdered>  · default · ReBAR canonical · requires explicit barriers
                                fence_release / fence_acquire model · matches Vulkan
                                VK_PIPELINE_STAGE_*_BIT semantics
      shared<T, NonCoherent>  · ReBAR-uncached · CPU writes immediately visible to GPU
                                but CPU reads of GPU writes are UB without barrier_g2c
                                use for one-way push from CPU (per-frame uniforms via ReBAR)
    
    barrier-primitives :
      barrier_c2g(s : shared<T, _>)  · CPU-write → GPU-read · MIR : cssl.gpu.barrier.c2g
      barrier_g2c(s : shared<T, _>)  · GPU-write → CPU-read · MIR : cssl.gpu.barrier.g2c
      barrier_full(s : shared<T, _>) · both directions · for shared<T, Coherent>
      
      lower-to :
        Vulkan : VkBufferMemoryBarrier with appropriate stage + access masks
        D3D12  : D3D12_RESOURCE_BARRIER_TYPE_UAV / _TRANSITION
        host   : memory fences (mfence on x86 · dmb ish on aarch64)
    
    cross-queue-semaphores :
      semaphore_signal(s : Semaphore, queue : QueueId) -> ()
      semaphore_wait(s : Semaphore, queue : QueueId) -> ()
      timeline_signal(t : TimelineSemaphore, value : u64) -> ()
      timeline_wait(t : TimelineSemaphore, min_value : u64) -> ()
      
      transfer<T> carries queue-tag : awaiting requires either same-queue or semaphore
  ⟧

§I CSSL-SYNTAX (concrete syntax additions)
  ⟦
    // declaration of GPU-resident value
    let camera_buf : gpu<Camera> = upload(camera).await()
    
    // ReBAR shared (for per-frame uniforms · the PRISM canonical pattern)
    let frame_uniforms : shared<FrameUniforms, NonCoherent> = alloc_shared(Layout::std430(), 1)?
    write_cpu(frame_uniforms, FrameUniforms { camera, time, frame_idx })
    barrier_c2g(frame_uniforms)
    // GPU side now reads frame_uniforms via the same handle (typed as gpu<FrameUniforms>
    // from @gpu context · automatically via the cross-domain arrow)
    
    // explicit upload + download (the v13 substrate.cssl pattern · cleaned up)
    fn pixel_correctness_test(ray_origin : vec3, ray_dir : vec3) -> f32 {
        let scene_gpu : gpu<Scene> = upload(scene).await()
        let result_buf : shared<f32, WeakOrdered> = alloc_shared(Layout::std430(), 1)?
        
        dispatch_compute(@gpu fn(o, d) -> () { /* writes result_buf */ }, ray_origin, ray_dir)
        
        barrier_g2c(result_buf)
        let result : f32 = read_cpu(result_buf)
        result
    }
    
    // async-compute · two-queue overlap (PRISM RT-pass + RC-build pattern)
    fn render_frame(scene : gpu<Scene>) -> () {
        let depth_buf : gpu<Buffer<f32>> = alloc_gpu(Layout::std430(), 1440*2560)?
        let cascade_buf : gpu<Cascade> = alloc_gpu(Layout::std430(), 1)?
        
        // RT pass on graphics queue · produces depth_buf
        let rt_done : Semaphore = dispatch_on(Queue::Graphics, @gpu rt_pass, scene, depth_buf)
        
        // RC build on compute queue · waits for rt_done
        let rc_done : Semaphore = dispatch_on(Queue::Compute, @gpu rc_build, scene, cascade_buf)
                                     .wait_for(rt_done)
        
        // composite waits for both
        let composite_done : Semaphore = dispatch_on(Queue::Graphics, @gpu composite, depth_buf, cascade_buf)
                                            .wait_for(rc_done)
        
        present(composite_done)
    }
  ⟧

§I INTERACTION-WITH-EXISTING-SPECS
  ⟦
    spec-03 (TYPES)         : memory-domain becomes part of the type · row-extends existing type-system
    spec-04 (EFFECTS)       : transfer-ops carry {GpuTransfer} effect · cross-queue ops carry {AsyncDispatch}
    spec-11 (IFC)           : Sensitive<*> labels propagate through transfer-ops · biometric-family
                              still absolutely-egress-banned across PCIe
    spec-12 (CAPABILITIES)  : Cap<Shared> + Cap<TransferAuth> new caps · iso ⊆ gpu<T> ⊆ shared<T> ⊆ box
    spec-14 (BACKEND)       : cssl.gpu.* MIR ops lower per-backend (Vulkan / D3D12 / Metal / WGSL)
    spec-16 (DUAL_SURFACE)  : @cross fn-signatures auto-derive memory-domain from call-site
    spec-24 (HOST_FFI)      : __cssl_gpu_* symbols add transfer + barrier surface
    spec-30_SUBSTRATE_v2    : Ω-Field cells live in shared<FieldCell, NonCoherent> by default
    spec-33 (F1..F6)        : F3 effect-rows extended with {GpuTransfer · AsyncDispatch · CrossQueue}
                              F5 IFC propagation across transfer-arrow strictly-checked
    spec-PRISM_v13          : direct consumer · ReBAR + async-compute architecture typed
  ⟧

§I NON-GOALS
  ⟦
    NG.01 · NOT a new GC or borrow-checker · existing §§ 12 Pony-6 capabilities cover ownership
    NG.02 · NOT a replacement for storage-class annotations on individual fields (those still
             work · per-struct-field storage-class is orthogonal to per-value memory-domain)
    NG.03 · NOT a unified-memory-model spec for Apple Silicon / ARM iGPU · those targets
             collapse gpu<T> ≡ T with zero-cost · per-target detail handled at codegen
    NG.04 · NOT a replacement for spec-04 effect-rows · transfers carry effects · this spec
             adds the type-distinction · effects ride on it
    NG.05 · NOT a multi-GPU / multi-node spec · single-device scope · multi-device deferred
    NG.06 · NOT shader-recompilation-on-domain-change · @gpu fns compile once · this spec
             changes the type-checking around them not the codegen pipeline
    NG.07 · NOT a defense against malicious-driver memory-corruption · the cap-system at
             OS-driver-boundary is out-of-scope (handled by spec-11 + OS layer)
  ⟧

