§I FAILURE-MODES
  ⟦
    FM.01 · scenario : host hardware does NOT support ReBAR · alloc_shared called
            detection : runtime probe at cssl-host-* init · build-emit GPU0010 warning
            mitigation : alloc_shared falls back to staged<T> pattern with synchronous upload
                          performance degraded but correctness preserved
            escalation : build-emit `--require-rebar` flag fails build at this scenario
    
    FM.02 · scenario : @gpu kernel reads shared<T, WeakOrdered> before CPU finished writing
            detection : compile-time check for barrier_c2g preceding read_gpu in same fn
                          + runtime SHADER_DEBUG validation layer assertion
            mitigation : compile-error GPU0003 · canonical "missing barrier" diagnostic
    
    FM.03 · scenario : transfer<T> awaited from a different queue without semaphore
            detection : compile-time queue-tag-tracking in transfer<T> · await callsite checks
            mitigation : compile-error GPU0005 · suggest semaphore_wait at error site
    
    FM.04 · scenario : Sensitive<gaze> value uploaded to gpu<T> then back to CPU for analytics
            detection : F5 IFC pass tracks label through transfer-arrow · ban triggers GPU0007
            mitigation : compile-error GPU0007 absolute · no Cap-override possible
                          (per PRIME-DIRECTIVE §1 + spec-11 biometric-family ban)
    
    FM.05 · scenario : transfer<T> dropped without await · linear-resource-leak
            detection : Pony-6 linear-tracking from spec-12 + audit at drop site
            mitigation : compile-error GPU0004 · suggest explicit cancel(t) if intentional
    
    FM.06 · scenario : Apple Silicon target · gpu<T> ≡ T should be zero-cost
            detection : target-feature query at codegen
            mitigation : backend specializes · gpu<T> lowers to no-op transfer · upload/download collapse
                          to identity (with appropriate memory-fence)
    
    FM.07 · scenario : developer ports v13 substrate without annotations · existing code breaks
            detection : opt-in module-level attribute @strict_memory_typing
            mitigation : without the attribute · ambient memory model preserved · existing code unchanged
                          with the attribute · enforcement engages · per-module migration cadence
    
    FM.08 · scenario : the spec accidentally over-restricts a legitimate pattern
            detection : adoption-monitoring during v13 PRISM integration
            mitigation : spec-amendment via lifecycle REVIEWED-state · expand allowed arrows
                          honest-failure : if the spec is wrong shape, amend rather than ship-around
  ⟧

