§I PRIOR-ART
  ⟦
    PA.01 · Halide pipeline · GPU/CPU split via schedule() · what-we-take : compile-time
             domain-distinction is feasible · what-we-diverge : Halide does it at schedule
             not at type · we make it a type-property for compile-time enforcement
    PA.02 · Taichi · ti.field / ti.Vector with memory-tier · what-we-take : per-allocation
             tier annotation · what-we-diverge : ti.field is library-level · we elevate to language
    PA.03 · Rust's Send + Sync · marker-trait approach to thread-safety · what-we-take : the
             pattern of "type-system enforces what mutex would otherwise enforce" ·
             what-we-diverge : memory-domain is more than a marker · it's a domain-distinct type
    PA.04 · CUDA __device__ + __host__ + __device_managed__ · what-we-take : the three-class
             memory taxonomy (gpu / cpu / shared) maps cleanly · what-we-diverge : CUDA still allows
             implicit deref · we forbid it · explicit transfers always
    PA.05 · Mojo @parameter + tensor-spec memory hierarchy · what-we-take : the layered-memory
             concept · what-we-diverge : Mojo doesn't yet enforce cross-domain bans · we do
    PA.06 · Vulkan VK_KHR_external_memory + ReBAR · what-we-take : the hardware capability we
             expose · this spec IS the language-level surface for the existing hardware feature
    PA.07 · Apple Metal MTLStorageMode · what-we-take : the four-mode taxonomy
             (Private · Shared · Memoryless · Managed) maps cleanly to gpu / shared / staged / coherent
  ⟧

